if not databank then
    system.print("ERROR: No databank connected!")
    unit.exit()
    return
end

local keys = databank.getKeyList()
system.print("=== HASKEY vs GETKEYS TEST ===")
system.print("Total keys from getKeyList(): " .. #keys)
system.print("")

-- Show first 10 keys from getKeyList()
system.print("First 10 keys from getKeyList():")
for i = 1, math.min(10, #keys) do
    system.print("  [" .. i .. "] '" .. keys[i] .. "'")
end
system.print("")

-- Test if those same keys work with hasKey()
system.print("Testing hasKey() on those same keys:")
for i = 1, math.min(10, #keys) do
    local key = keys[i]
    local result = databank.hasKey(key)
    system.print("  hasKey('" .. key .. "') = " .. tostring(result) .. " (raw: " .. result .. ")")
end
system.print("")

-- Test specific ore keys
local testKeys = {"hematite", "bauxite", "coal", "quartz", "chromite"}
system.print("Testing specific ore keys:")
for _, key in ipairs(testKeys) do
    local result = databank.hasKey(key)
    system.print("  hasKey('" .. key .. "') = " .. tostring(result) .. " (raw: " .. result .. ")")
    
    -- Also check if it's in the getKeyList() results
    local foundInList = false
    for _, listKey in ipairs(keys) do
        if listKey == key then
            foundInList = true
            break
        end
    end
    system.print("    Found in getKeyList: " .. tostring(foundInList))
end

unit.exit()
